tered","2 Tbsp lemon juice","2 pinches fine sea salt, or to taste","2 pinches ground black pepper, or to taste, plus extra for sprinkling"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["100 g smoked salmon, sliced","1 lemon, cut in wedges"]}],"id":"r304668","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-40NAURQ0TH4\/XZafZW0rnoI\/AAAAAAAAgt4\/scZpLqF8ncorZw259KufGTAQr6FbR6i0QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_mRA2V9u30vzeiR6g.png","title":"Seeded Breakfast Bread with Avocado Ricotta Spread and Smoked Salmon","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17.7 g","fat":"27.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"22.8 g","calories":"1768 kJ \/ 425 kcal"},"usefulItems":"loaf tin (900 g\/2 lb), wire rack, toaster, baking paper, skewer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Cooled bread can be tightly wrapped and stored for <nobr>3 days,<\/nobr> or frozen for up to <nobr>1 month.<\/nobr>","Our version of the ever-popular avocado on toast has a slight twist with the addition of ricotta. Served on a seedy and nutritious loaf that requires no proving time, it makes a great option when you want fresh bread in the morning. Topping the toast with omega 3-rich salmonalso boosts the protein, keeping you fuller for longer.","Could also be topped with a poached egg. See <i>Smashed Plum Tomato Bruschetta with Poached Eggs<\/i> for method."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","3h 20m","6 portions"]}